# Frontend workflow

## Run

From `frontend/`:

```bash
npm run dev          # Vite on http://localhost:5173, proxies /api -> :8001
npm run test:watch   # Vitest watcher
npm run typecheck    # tsc --noEmit
npm run build        # tsc --noEmit && vite build
```

Override the backend target with `VITE_BACKEND_URL` (see `vite.config.ts`).

## Tests (Vitest + Testing Library)

- Place tests next to the unit under test as `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`.
- Keep `npm run test:watch` running while editing — that's the inner loop.
- One-shot run before commit: `npm test`.

```bash
npx vitest run src/<path>/<file>.test.tsx   # single file
```

## Style

- Functional components only; extract reusable logic into hooks under
  `src/hooks/` and pure helpers into `src/lib/`.
- Server state goes through TanStack Query; don't roll your own caching.
- API calls live in `src/lib/` (typed wrappers around axios). UI components
  must not call axios directly.
- Always send the CSRF header on mutating requests — the shared API client
  already does this; don't bypass it.
- Run `npm run typecheck` before handing off — `npm run build` will fail on
  type errors.
- Don't add narrating comments; only comment non-obvious intent.
